OL,5,Cout
OL,7,FThe court heard he has a previous
OL,8,Fexcess alcohol conviction from 2009
OL,9,Fbut provided a sample at the time of
OL,10,Fthat offence.
OL,12,FWhen asked about his financial
OL,13,Fcircumstances, the court heard Gough
OL,14,Fearns a net income of around #2,500 a
OL,15,Fweek.
OL,17,FMagistrates fined him #4,166 and
OL,18,Fordered him to pay a surcharge of
OL,19,F#1,666 and court costs of #85. He was
OL,20,Falso banned from driving for 16 months.
